casebody.data:
Norman S. Chapin v. John J. Tynan, Commissioner of Motor Vehicles, et al.

King, C. J., Alcorn, House, Thim and Ryan, Js.

Argued December 9 decided December 9, 1969 H. David Leventhal, for the appellant (plaintiff). Stephen J. O’Neill, assistant attorney general, with whom, on the brief, was Robert K. Killian, attorney general, for the appellee (named defendant). George F. Lowman, with whom were John F. Spindler and, on the brief, James M. Barton, for the appellee (defendant R. L. Polk and Company). Per Curiam.

There is no error.
